cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze user reviews and predict Quality in Use (QU) indicators. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of Latent Semantic Analysis (LSA) and its subspace suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on software quality and risk assessment could also place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
